<H3> <TI>   `Los Granaderos' To Guarantee `Normal' Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2802200594 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1800 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2802200594 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "NTC Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] Los Granaderos is the name of the 100 men of the 
antiguerrilla warfare specialized police whose mission is to 
guarantee the normal development of the forthcoming elections. 
  These nine antiguerrilla police officers are part of an 
elite 
group with a specific mission: To halt subversive attacks 
before and after the elections. Los Granaderos, as they are 
called in combat, just completed a quick course at the Gabriel 
Gonzalez School in El Espinal, Tolima Department, a few hours 
ago. 
  Los Granaderos simulated a patrol action, and they tested 
their reaction in the face of an ambush. These men have a very 
clear idea of their mission. 
  [Begin General Octavio Vargas Silva, National Police 
director, recording] The guerrillas should be duly warned we are 
aptly prepared and armed to counter any attack. We are going to 
do to them what David did to Goliath: wipe them out. [end 
recording] 
  These nine Granaderos are part of a group of 100 men who as 
of next week will be posted at strategic points. The police 
director announced other measures this morning for guaranteeing 
calm during the next elections. 
  [Begin Vargas Silva recording] All vacations, furloughs, and 
permits have been suspended so that as of yesterday and through 
13 March most of the police force will be on the streets, in 
those places we consider sensitive or vulnerable. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

