<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Canadian Foreign Minister Begins Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   End To U.S. Embargo of Cuba Urged </H4>
<F P=102> LD0203151594 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 
1430 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0203151594 </F>
<F P=104>  Montreal Radio Canada International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Canada and Mexico have agreed to work together to 
push for an end to the U.S.-imposed trade embargo against Cuba. 
Canada's foreign minister, Andre Ouellet, and his Mexican 
counterpart, Manuel Tello, met in Mexico City yesterday, and 
they said it is time to convince the U.S. to end the isolation 
of Cuba. Neither Canada nor Mexico observe the U.S.-led 
embargo. The embargo has been in force since the 1960's. 

</TEXT>

