<H3> <TI>   Troops From 3-80 Northern Front Begin Demobilizing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0303132394 Managua Radio Nicaragua Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0303132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Troops from the rebel 3-80 Northern Front began 
demobilizing 2 March. An initial group of 100 men will become 
the guardians of public order in the municipalities of Quilali, 
Wiwili, Murra, and Jicaro, following an intensive training 
process that will begin 7 March at the Manauga Police Academy. 
  The demobilization of a second group of the 3-80 Northern 
Front is scheduled for 16 March. At that time, another 220 men 
will demobilize, which, together with the initial group, will 
add up to 50 percent of the rebel troops. 
  The last contingent will demobilize on 16 April, at which 
time the rebel leader, Jose Angel Talavera, alias El Chacal, 
will also disarm. 

</TEXT>

