<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Candidates Perez, Carles Leading </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0303232694 Panama City LA PRENSA in Spanish 2 Mar 94 p 1A </F>
<F P=103> PA0303232694 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City LA PRENSA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Orlando Mendieta C.] </F>
  [Text] A poll requested by LA PRENSA and conducted by the 
Dichter &amp; Neira consulting company has revealed that 
presidential candidates Ernesto Perez Balladares, who garnered 
the support of 37.3 of those polled, and Ruben Dario Carles, 
with 20.5 percent of those polled, have the largest number of 
followers in their bid for the presidency of Panama. 
  The survey was conducted nationwide, and 1,753 people were 
polled from 25 to 27 February. This is the first poll conducted 
since 8 February when the Electoral Tribunal closed the 
registration period for candidates to elective office. According 
to the poll, Perez Balladares continues to be the favorite 
candidate, with his support increasing by 5 percent. The poll 
revealed that if the elections were held today, 37.3 percent of 
the people would vote for Perez Balladares. This reflects an 
increase in the number of followers of the PRD [Democratic 
Revolutionary Party] candidate. He registered a 32.1 percent 
popularity rate in the last poll taken on 27 January. 
  Meanwhile, Ruben Carles, presidential candidate for Molirena 
[Nationalist Republican Liberal Movement], Morena [National 
Renewal Movement], and Civic Renewal parties, came in second 
place with 20.5 percent. Carles' popularity rate rose 7.3 
percent from the previous poll, in which he placed third with 
13.2 percent of the votes. 
  Ruben Blades, Papa Egoro Movement's presidential candidate, 
suffered the largest decrease in popularity in this poll by 
registering only a 9.9 percent popularity rate, which placed him 
third among the candidates chosen to win the 8 May election. 
Blades registered 18.9 percent in late January. 
  As for the other presidential candidates, the poll showed, 
in 
descending order, that Mireya de Gruber of the Arnulfist Party 
registered 8.1 percent, Eduardo Vallarino of the Christian 
Democratic Party (PDC) registered 3 percent, Samuel Lewis 
Galindo of Solidarity Party registered 2.8 percent, and Jose 
Salvador Munoz of the Doctrinaire Panamenist Party registered 
0.2 percent. Compared to the previous poll, Gruber's popularity 
rating decreased by 1.7 percent. Vallarino, meanwhile, in his 
first appearance in a poll showed a 3-percent popularity rate, 
which is lower than the 4 percent that his fellow party member 
Ricardo Arias Calderon registered before withdrawing his 
candidacy due to health problems. As for Lewis Galindo, his 
popularity increased by 2 percent, while Munoz appeared for the 
first time in the voters' preference list. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

