<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Brazilian President Arrives To Meet Caldera </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0403014594 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 2350 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0403014594 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Brazilian President Itamar Franco arrived at the 
Simon Bolivar international airport at 1705. He is accompanied 
by Foreign Minister Celso Amorim and a group of high-ranking 
officials from his cabinet. Itamar Franco is the first head of 
state to be received by Rafael Caldera as Venezuelan president 
after taking office one month ago. Sources close to the 
Brazilian Government said the objective of a working meeting on 
Friday is to develop the economic foundations for the creation 
of a trade agreement to be known as Merconorte. Despite the 
importance of the meeting, the presidents do not plan to sign 
any agreements since the two countries already have more than 36 
agreements ranging from cultural exchanges to technical and 
trade cooperation. 

</TEXT>

