<H3> <TI>   Russian Association Chairman on Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0403194594 Havana Radio Havana Cuba in Spanish 0000 GMT 4 
March 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0403194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Havana Cuba </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lev (Mogilevskiy), chairman of the Russian-Cuban 
International Economic Commercial Association, said his 
association will essentially be the strategic group for 
cooperation between Russia and the largest island in the 
Antilles. In an interview with the Russian news agency 
ITAR-TASS, (Mogilevskiy) said the association must solve current 
problems on the renewal of air and maritime transportation and 
development of the tourism industry. He added that 
Russian-Cuban projects include the creation of a mixed 
consortium to extract and refine oil, petrochemistry, and the 
manufacture of minerals and fertilizers. 

</TEXT>

