Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Colombian Ambassador to Cuba (Ricardo Santamaria 
Salamanca) said today that Cuba and Colombia will reach 
important agreements this quarter that will help create a 
dynamic scenario for business deals and the influx of capital 
and businessmen. 
  The ambassador also stressed the growing pace of 
negotiations 
between the two countries in various sectors of the economy, 
science, culture, and health. 
