<H3> <TI>   Robaina Departs on Seven-Country Asian Trip </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0603223494 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 1800 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0603223494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ruben Pino] </F>
  [Text] On the evening of 5 March, Foreign Minister Roberto 
Robaina departed on a trip to Indonesia. Robaina is accompanied 
by an official delegation from the Foreign Ministry [Minrex]. 
  Robaina told journalists at Jose Marti International Airport 
that the trip will include seven Asian countries: Indonesia, 
Laos, Cambodia, Malaysia, India, Myanmar [Burma], and Vietnam. 
Robaina is seeking to spread the truth about the Cuban project. 
  [Begin recording] [Pino] What are Minrex's expectations from 
these meetings? 
  [Robaina] I believe the expectations are part of everything 
that has been done, I do not want to say in the last year, 
rather in the past. Nowadays we live at a faster tempo and thus 
we need to explain more energetically what we are doing and to 
keep abreast of what is happening in the world. I believe that 
Asia is no exception in this diplomatic offensive. I plan to 
listen to many opinions. I believe that there is much to learn 
from this part of the world and much to contribute. This is the 
main goal of the trip. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

