<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aristide Spokesman Explains Flynn Visit to Haiti </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0403195494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0403195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Aristide's spokesman Jean-Claude Martineau 
has pointed out that the visit of the U.S. ambassador to the 
Vatican was aimed at verifying the distribution of humanitarian 
aid in Haiti. According to Martineau, shortly before his visit 
to Haiti, Mr. Flynn had a conversation with President Bill 
Clinton regarding the restoration of democracy to Haiti within 
the scope of the Governors Island agreement. 
  For his part, in Paris President Aristide discussed with Mr. 
Flynn the Vatican's participation in the process of restoring 
democracy to Haiti. He pointed out that the conversation with 
the envoy to the Vatican was positive. 

</TEXT>

