<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Cardoso Candidacy Gaining Strength </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0403185494 Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 3 
Mar 94 p A6 </F>

<F P=103> PY0403185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Estadao Column" by Cristiana Lobo] </F>
  [Text] A recent poll shows a substantial growth in [Finance 
Minister] Fernando Henrique Cardoso's candidacy for the 
presidential race: He moved from 6 percent, a level at which he 
remained stable for some months, to 12 percent of the electoral 
preference, climbing to third place in this race. 
  PT [Workers Party] candidate Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva still 
is the favorite, even though he lost 3 percentage points: He 
fell from 30 to 27 percent of the votes. PPR [Progressive 
Renewal Party candidate] Paulo Maluf remains in second place 
with 17 percent of the electoral preference. 
  After this poll, the PSDB [Brazilian Social Democracy Party] 
will press Fernando Henrique Cardoso even more to leave his post 
by the end of the month in order to run for Itamar Franco's job. 
Meanwhile, the PSDB says the decision remains with the minister 
himself. 
  Senator Mario Covas said: "Fernando will entirely let events 
take their course. He is a man with public spirit. Thus, he 
will decide if he stays or leaves. He is not a vulgar 
opportunist." 
  President Itamar Franco's advisers already are acquainted 
with the poll. During the past few days, Franco has discussed 
this issue with politicians and has begun to consider a 
replacement. The PSDB is very interested in this issue because 
the economic program's success depends on Cardoso's management. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

