<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Record Agricultural Harvest Expected This Year </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0403161494 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 1000 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0403161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This year's agricultural harvest will be 
approximately 7 percent higher than last year's, according to an 
IBGE [Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics] survey. 
  It is estimated that 74 million metric tons will be 
harvested 
this year, which represents a new national record. According to 
IBGE experts, seven of the eight products included in the survey 
will have a good harvest. 

</TEXT>

