<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Extends State of Emergency in Apurimac </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0603192994 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1735 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0603192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lima, 6 Mar (DPA) -- The government extended for 60 
days the state of emergency in four provinces of Apurimac 
Department, southeast of Lima, today. The measure, published in 
the official newspaper EL PERUANO, stated certain constitutional 
guarantees will be suspended and that the Armed Forces will be 
in charge of internal order. The decree stemmed from the need 
to facilitate antiterrorist operations in that department. 

</TEXT>

