<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Vice President Heads Visiting Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0403211194 Lima EL COMERCIO in Spanish 23 Feb 94 p A4 </F>
<F P=103> PY0403211194 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima EL COMERCIO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Without Confirmation" column by Alfonso Baella] </F>
  [Text] Mr. Kim Pyong-sik has been in Lima since 20 
February. He is visiting from the DPRK. Mr. Kim Pyong-sik 
introduced himself as the chairman of the North Korean Social 
Democratic Party's Central Committee, although this party in 
reality depends on the communist Korean Workers' Party 
supporting Kim Il-song's dictatorship. In fact, the strange 
visitor has also been one of the DPRK vice presidents since his 
election to this post on 11 December 1993. 
  During his visit to Lima, Kim Pyong-sik, who arrived with a 
four-man entourage, met various personalities. His mission in 
Lima is not exactly known, but it has been leaked that he would 
afterwards tour Latin America, visiting Ecuador, Uruguay, and 
eventually Paraguay and Venezuela. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

