<F P=102>  PA0603164994 Managua Sistema Nacional de Television Network 
in Spanish 0200 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0603164994 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Sistema Nacional de Television Network 
in Spanish 0200 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] Norway and Nicaragua have signed a five-year 
technical advisory assistance agreement in different areas. 
Twenty-one Norwegian technicians are working in various regions 
of the country. Milviana Jerez has filed a report: 
  [Begin recording] [Jerez] Tom Tyrihjell, resident 
representative of the Norwegian Development Authority and Sergio 
Mario Blandon, acting foreign cooperation minister, signed the 
five-year agreement. The average cost for each technician who 
will provide technical assistance is $80,000. 
  [Tyrihjell, in progress] ...that is very important, because 
it represents a relationship more than technical cooperation. 
It is a relationship at the human level by Norwegian 
technicians who want to aid a developing country and return to 
their country with new experience. 
  [Jerez] The Norwegian technicians are lending their 
technical 
assistance in the First, Fourth, Fifth, and Rio San Juan Regions. 
  [Blandon, in progress] ...is really praiseworthy, because 
while we have difficult campaigns that hinder the cooperation 
process in Nicaragua, we are receiving encouragement from 
countries, such as yours, that are willing to help this country. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

