<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chamber of Deputies Approves Bank Deposit Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0403142794 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 2350 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0403142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Excerpts] The bill on a special law protecting bank 
depositors and regulating emergencies in financial institutions 
was approved today during a second debate at the Chamber of 
Deputies. 
  The second debates on the special law lasted approximately 
12 
hours; it was finally approved at 1230 today, after an agreement 
was reached on the final procedures. 
  The law, which has 70 articles, stipulates the titles of 
Banco Latino depositors will be recognized regardless of the 
legal body that issued it, as long as the transaction was made 
at Banco Latino. The law also permits the flexibility of 
financial aid [auxilio financiero] and expands control of banks 
receiving financial aid to the point the board of directors can 
be replaced while assistance is being received. Fogade [Deposit 
Guarantee Fund] will be responsible for 4 million bolivares. 
[passage omitted] 
  The bill approved by the Chamber of Deputies was sent this 
afternoon to the Senate, where, as the Congress president said, 
it will be given constitutional urgency; therefore, the Senate 
debates will begin 3 March. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

