<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Denies Negative Placet Given to U.S. Envoy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0403200894 Santa Fe de Bogota EL NUEVO SIGLO in Spanish 27 
Feb 94 p2 </F>

<F P=103> PA0403200894 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota EL NUEVO SIGLO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Capsules" column] </F>
  [Text] There is great discontent over the Clinton 
administration's appointment of Myles Frenchette as the new U.S. 
ambassador to Colombia. Frenchette was responsible for the 
failure of the Coffee Pact, which harmed the country greatly. 
In addition, the Brazilian Government did not accept him as 
ambassador. Despite press reports, the Foreign Ministry has 
denied the placet was given to this enemy of the world's coffee 
growers. 

</TEXT>

