<F P=102>  PA0603192894 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1800 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0603192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jose Penagos; from the "NTC News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Luis Fernando Correa, regional director of the 
Technical Investigations Corp of the Medellin Public 
Prosecutor's Office, was murdered at 1030 today in (Calasasa), 
Medellin. The investigator was intercepted by several men 
traveling in a white Renault Nine. 
  Correa was in charge of escorting Nicolas Escobar, son of 
Roberto Escobar, out of the country; he also personally directed 
the transfer of Pablo Escobar's family to Santa Fe de Bogota. 
  Correa was going to pick someone up at this residence in 
western Medellin when two cars intercepted him; one of them was 
white, a Renault, with no particular characteristics, which is 
being sought, particularly in western Medellin, by the 
authorities. 

</TEXT>

