<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Haitians Demonstrate Outside Aristide-UN Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0703233194 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1145 
GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0703233194 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President in exile Jean-Bertrand Aristide considers 
the legislators' plan not in compliance with the Governors 
Island accord signed in New York last July, and even contrary to 
this accord in the context of reestablishing democracy in Haiti. 
This statement was made during a meeting with the UN secretary 
general. Jean-Bertrand Aristide spoke for more than an hour with 
the UN secretary general while several thousand Haitians 
demonstrated near UN headquarters in support of the president in 
exile. 
  It should be recalled that on the previous day, 4 March, the 
four countries, Friends of Haiti, had submitted to the UN 
Security Council a draft resolution reinforcing international 
sanctions against Haiti. The draft resolution provides for a 
total commercial embargo, except for food and medicine, the 
banning of non-commercial flights to or from Haiti, as well as 
some restrictions on travel by the authors of the coup d'etat 
and their relatives abroad. The UN Security Council is due to 
make a decision on this resolution within 15 days. 

</TEXT>

