<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Envoy `Sensitive,' Optimistic </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0703233294 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0703233294 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] U.S. Ambassador to Port-au-Prince William Lacy 
Swing said he is sensitive to the concerns of President Aristide 
who has rejected the plan proposed by Haitian parliamentarians 
as a resolution to the crisis. Swing said that he is optimistic 
about the chances of finding a solution to the crisis. He 
mentioned four reasons that should favor a quick outcome to the 
crisis: the context of change of political systems in the 
hemisphere, the consensus of the four countries called Friends 
of Haiti, the availability of massive economic aid, and the 
Governors Island agreement. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

