<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Delegates Witness URNG Attack on Quiche Base </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0803044894 Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 5 Mar 94 
p 6 </F>

<F P=103> PA0803044894 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Army Information Office has reported that 
terrorists of the self-styled Guatemalan National Revolutionary 
Unity (URNG) attacked the Aczumbal patrol base in Quiche while 
several UN Human Rights delegates were boarding a light airplane. 
  The source added that the airplane, registration TG-CAC and 
piloted by Gerardo Poitevan, carried 18 delegates, including Dr. 
Sergio Viva Scheel, a UN human rights consultant. This fact was 
later corroborated by Hugo Leon Mejia del Aguila, the human 
rights office assistant in Nebaj, Quiche. 
  The visitors witnessed the attack and saw how the rebels 
fired indiscriminately without regard for the fact that 
civilians were present in a flagrant violation of human rights, 
the Army report states. 
  The Guatemalan Army reported that this attack shows once 
again the guerrillas' lack of respect for the sacred right to 
life. After the rebel attack, the visiting delegations traveled 
without further incidents. The delegates did say they would 
report the event at the international level because the URNG's 
criminal action exposed its lack of political willingness to 
promote peace, the report concludes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

