<H3> <TI>   Armed Forces Official: Corps in `Optimum Condition' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0603154294 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 0345 GMT 6 Mar 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA0603154294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Major General Ulises Rosales del Toro, first vice 
minister of the Revolutionary Armed Forces (FAR), said today 
this corps is in optimum condition to fulfill its mission due to 
its high cohesion and combative readiness. 
  In a meeting with journalists on the occasion of Cuban Press 
Day, which will be held on 14 March, Rosales del Toro said that 
the FAR are in their best stage of development, according to a 
National Information Agency report. 
  The General Staff chief argued the Armed Forces have a 
commander in chief, Fidel Castro, who is capable enough to 
continue leading the revolution, a minister, Raul Castro, who 
has much experience, and a corps of officers forged by 
revolutionary struggles. 
  Regarding the education of the new generations, the general 
cited journalists' role. Rosales del Toro, also a member of the 
Communist Party of Cuba Politburo, said the press must fight 
every formality and work for the defense of the country. 

</TEXT>

