<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Decision Yet on Buying Mirage-5 Fighters </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0803032294 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2338 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY0803032294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Santiago, 7 Mar (EFE) -- The Chilean Air Force 
(FACh) commander, General Ramon Vega, today explained that this 
institution still has not decided whether it will purchase 
Mirage-5 fighters from Brussels as reported by the media. 
  The new acquisitions fall within an overall plan to 
modernize 
the Chilean Armed Forces' equipment, and in the FACh's case they 
are to replace the old Hawker Hunter fighters and other aircraft. 
  Gen. Vega said there is still nothing definite about the 
purchase of Mirage fighters, although he admitted "it is a 
possibility the FACh is assessing." 
  Vega made this statement after a ceremony in which he 
received a Spanish-made CASA transportation aircraft, model 
C-212, the first of a group of six to replace the Twin Otter 
aircraft that operate in southern Chile. 

</TEXT>

