<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Says Scheduled Gore Visit `Very Positive' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0803023994 Sao Paulo GAZETA MERCANTIL in Portuguese 7 Mar 
94 p 5 </F>

<F P=103> PY0803023994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo GAZETA MERCANTIL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Maria Helena Tachinardi in La Guaira, Venezuela] </F>
  [Text] Brazilian Foreign Minister Celso Amorim described as 
very positive the visit U.S. Vice President Al Gore will make to 
Brazil on 21 March, when he will be received by President Itamar 
Franco. On the night of 3 March, Amorim confirmed here to 
GAZETA that Gore will meet Franco. 
  After visiting Argentina, Gore will come immediately to 
Brazil, where he will discuss topics such as the environment, 
sustainable development, and the U.S.-Latin American summit to 
be held in Washington this year. 
  Amorim said Gore will visit Brazil in an atmosphere of 
positive bilateral relations as a result of the U.S. decision to 
refrain from imposing trade sanctions on Brazil as part of its 
quest for ensuring protection of intellectual property rights. 
Commenting on this issue -- which was resolved on 25 February, 
Amorim noted that Brazil benefited from the new framework 
created on the subject, that is, the wording of "TRIPPS" 
(Trade-Related Intellectual Property Protection System) 
negotiated under the GATT Uruguay Round. 
  Amorim also noted that Brazil has made progress in this area 
and that his willingness to go to Washington on 16 February just 
to discuss the matter with U.S. Trade Representative Mickey 
Kantor -- during a 90-minute meeting -- created a good 
impression in the United States. Speaking to this newspaper, 
Amorim said: "They felt that we have shown interest." Amorim 
said a new positive stage has started in our relations that is 
"very favorable for cooperation in sustainable development and 
investments. Potential issues of conflict have been eliminated." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-10493 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat045_m_94003" </HT>


